RACE.FOOTNOTES: UNEXPECTED OUTCOME (IRE) pressed the issue inside in the beginning, was then content to track the pacesetter on the turn, angled out three wide gaining momentum for the drive with two furlongs remaining, found his best stride at the eighth pole and went on by the frontrunner to draw away in deep stretch. VIDEO VIDA took command narrowly early on, opened up on horses through the turn, began to get leg weary in mid stretch still not switching leads, offered little resistance to the winner at the sixteenth pole and held on for the place share at the wire. IT'S ME MARIO broke inwards to start, was on hold inside behind the chasing pack throughout the turn, rallied when a seam opened up four wide at the quarter marker, posed a threat four wide outside runners in upper stretch but could no match strides with the winner late. IGNITE THE STORM broke slow seeing field inside in the early going, was under a tight hold between rivals entering the turn, roused with five sixteenths to go and passed tired runners inside through the lane. SING DIXIE settled near the rear three deep in the beginning, put in a mild run outside three wide starting at the half mile marker, was in contention at the three eighths pole, angled six wide for the drive but had little to give to the finish. TORY'S HOLIDAY was in a good spot early tracking the top pair down the back straight, was ridden trying to keep position behind the frontrunner with rivals on either side, offered little response by the quarter pole and gave way in upper stretch. PRETZLICK stumbled shortly after the break, co-trailed outside down the backside, could not get interested running on the turn and was not a factor finishing on the fence down the lane.

SUGAR RAY prompted outside leaving the chute, continued to press the issue down the backstretch forcing an honest pace, was ridden for more at the quarter marker between foes, offered little gain and faded in upper stretch.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: IT'S A FLUKE quickly took control while in hand down the backstretch, was left alone unchallenged setting a soft pace throughout the turn, rider took a look back in upper stretch looking for rivals, found none and was hand ridden to the wire for the easy win. JACK settled three deep outside in the early going, took closer order to the winner rallying four wide midway on the turn, looked to be the only one who could threaten in the six path at the top of the stretch but the winner was lone gone and had to settle for second best on this day. MIDNIGHT TEMPESTA tracked with rivals on either side down the backside, chased the pacesetting winner on the turn, battled on in upper stretch for second, faded for that at the sixteenth pole and held on for the show award at the wire. MOON OVER EGBERT settled in the third flight between runners, made little headway on the turn, could see the field in the five path straightening out for the drive, continued to keep an even pace in mid stretch and got up for a small share late. HYGGE stalked on the rail in the third flight down the back straight, saved ground throughout the turn making little impact, split foes at the eighth pole and showed good late energy to the wire to be involved for the minors. CLIVE CROSS chased the frontrunner on the rail down the backstretch, was shuffled back on the fence losing a few positions on the turn, was scrubbed on inside two furlongs from the finish to be in the mix for a small share and could not find more and stalled in the final furlong on the rail. LITTLE DOMI was allowed to settle trailing the field in the beginning, caught up to the field running in hand three wide with three eighths to go, angled out seven wide for the stretch drive and made little impression to the finish. HEY LUIGI tracked three deep outside down the backside, was nudged on the keep pace between others with five sixteenths to go, offered little turn of foot five wide at the quarter pole and retreated in mid stretch.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: CONMAN tracked the top pair four wide on the first turn, had a perfect set up watching the front two duel down the back straight, collared the softened up frontrunner in upper stretch, went on by at the eighth pole and was drawing away nicely at the finish. LIFETIME OF CHANCE broke out at the start, angled inside saving ground on the first turn to stalk the leaders, rated near the back in no hurry down the backstretch, began to quicken around runners midpoint on the turn in a bold move, shifted out six wide for the drive and determinedly ran on but could not gain on the winner and settled for second best. EYES ON THE KING brushed inside rival at the start, prompted the leader four wide into the first turn, forced the pace outside under lively fractions down the backside, appeared to be giving way between foes at the quarter pole five wide and resurged at the furlong marker to be involved for the place share at the wire. MEHLEK trailed on the fence in the early going, still could see the field running at the half, began to pick up horses two wide outside at the quarter pole, shifted out in the four path at the top of the lane, shifted inside at the furlong marker and closed late to get up for a minor share at the finish line. SIR LANCELOT was brushed at the start, took the field three wide entering the first turn, was hounded outside throughout the backstretch, opened up on the early pace rival midway on the final turn, was collared by the closing winner outside in mid stretch, could not find another gear to repel the challenge and tired in the last sixteenth. KEEN FLATTER stalked five wide outside foes into the first turn, was content near the back of the pack down the backside, was roused with three furlongs to keep up to the front pack, could not offer a rally and was empty for the drive to the wire.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: QUITE READY tracked in the second flight on the fence, was on hold behind the front duo throughout the turn, was looking for running room in the three path in upper stretch, finally found a seam bursting through splitting rivals at the furlong marker and surged right at the wire to get up in the last jump for the victory in a well timed stretch rally. WOODBINE WAY tracked in the second flight outside, rallied to offer a bid three wide at the five sixteenths pole, swung out five wide turning for home having clear running room, had a slim lead with a sixteenth remaining but could not find another gear late and lost the nod at the wire for the win. GALVASTON prompted outside in the early stages, hounded the pace while running comfortably outside throughout the turn, bid four wide at the quarter pole, poked his head in front with three sixteenths remaining, began to weaken a touch between foes at the sixteenth but still finished late to hold for show in the end. FOUR ACES HIGH was checked on the rail soon after the start to trail the compact field down the backside, regrouped to be with the field running in hand at the hand, was looking for running room behind horses turning for home, lost its path four wide at the furlong marker, shifted out losing momentum with a sixteenth to go and could not recover in time to pose a threat at the finish. KAWACATOOSE was hustled to lead this field down the backstretch, continued up front having a slim advantage inside on the turn, was collared outside straightening out for the drive, fought on stubbornly until the eighth pole and gave way in deep stretch.
